                            <comment id="12895426" author="niallp" created="Wed, 4 Aug 2010 21:16:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The resetCount method was added with the synchronized keyword:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/viewvc?view=revision&amp;amp;revision=140583&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/viewvc?view=revision&amp;amp;revision=140583&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;The getCount() methods were synchronzied later for the changes &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/IO-84&quot; title=&quot;Many classes are limited to length of stream &amp;lt; 2 GB, and behave incorrectly on larger streams&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;IO-84&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;IO-84&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; - but theres no mention of why&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/viewvc?view=revision&amp;amp;revision=462818&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/viewvc?view=revision&amp;amp;revision=462818&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;I agree the syncronization is incomplete and could probably be removed. Seems like a minor thing though so. I&apos;m assigning this to 2.x.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
